<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/about.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0/font-awesome.min.css">
    <title>About Tickety | The Evolution of Entertainment</title>
</head>
<body>
    <%- include('partials/header') %>

    <div class="bg-glow-layer"></div>

    <main class="about-wrapper">
        <section class="hero-container">
            <div class="reveal-box">
                <span class="tagline">Next-Gen Ticketing Ecosystem</span>
                <h1 class="main-title">Redefining <span>Human</span> Connection.</h1>
                <p class="hero-sub">Tickety is not just a platform; it’s a mission to democratize the live event industry through transparency and speed.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="mega-story">
            <div class="story-text">
                <h2>The Genesis of Tickety</h2>
                <p>In early 2024, our founders noticed a recurring flaw in the event-tech space: <b>The "Hidden Fee" Trap.</b> Most platforms lured fans with low base prices, only to add massive convenience charges at checkout. Tickety was conceptualized to break this cycle.</p>
                <p>We built a system where <b>Integrity meets Innovation.</b> By utilizing distributed database management and high-frequency inference engines, we ensure that the booking process remains as fast as the speed of light.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="side-stats">
                <div class="stat-box"><h3>₹10 + 1%</h3><p>Flat Fee Model</p></div>
                <div class="stat-box"><h3>< 3s</h3><p>Checkout Speed</p></div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="philosophy-grid">
            <div class="p-card">
                <i class="fas fa-bullseye"></i>
                <h3>Our Vision</h3>
                <p>To become the global standard for event accessibility, ensuring every fan, regardless of their location, has an equal opportunity to experience live music, comedy, and theater.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="p-card">
                <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i>
                <h3>Innovation Core</h3>
                <p>We believe technology should be invisible. Our AI (Tickety AI) works in the background to curate personalized experiences while our 3D seat-mapping provides ultimate clarity.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="tech-stack-section">
            <div class="tech-header">
                <h2>Built for the Future</h2>
                <p>Explore the architecture that powers your bookings.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tech-grid">
                <div class="tech-item">
                    <h4>Node.js Architecture</h4>
                    <p>Event-driven, non-blocking I/O model for handling massive ticket drops without crashes.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tech-item">
                    <h4>MongoDB Atlas</h4>
                    <p>NoSQL cloud storage ensuring high availability and scalability for global events.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tech-item">
                    <h4>Groq AI Inference</h4>
                    <p>Leveraging LPU technology for near-instantaneous customer support and event discovery.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tech-item">
                    <h4>AES Encryption</h4>
                    <p>Military-grade security for your dynamic QR tickets to prevent fraud and scalping.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="roadmap">
            <h2>The Roadmap: 2026 & Beyond</h2>
            <div class="roadmap-container">
                <div class="road-point"><span>Q3 2025</span><p>Initial Launch with Comedy & Music Segments.</p></div>
                <div class="road-point active"><span>Q1 2026</span><p>AI Chatbot Integration & 3D Seating Engine.</p></div>
                <div class="road-point"><span>Q4 2026</span><p>Global Expansion & Blockchain Ticket Verification.</p></div>
            </div>
        </section>

    </main>

    <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>